dct_description_sm: The Islands of Borabora, Raiatea, Tahaa and Huahine are taken from the French survey of 1882-86 ; Motu Iti is from a sketch by Dr. Martin L. Grant in 1931.
Depths shown by soundings; relief by hachures and spot heights.
Shows shoals, reefs, small islands, vegetation, drainage.
